    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Farewell to a Club</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jerome Weinberger letter deplores New York University's move to force closing of Bottom Line (Jan 26 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Bottom Line, a Place Where the Music Always Came First'' (Critic's Notebook, Jan. 26):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Bottom Line, a Place Where the Music Always Came First'' (Critic's Notebook, Jan. 26):</p>
        <p>I don't think New York University quite grasps the damage the forced closing of the Bottom Line has done to the prestige and reputation of N.Y.U. within the community. It is as if N.Y.U. were metastasizing.</p>
        <p>JEROME WEINBERGER  New York, Jan. 26, 2004</p>
      </block>
